{
  "texts": [
    "For the left-to-right inclusion, suppose x ̸ ∈ (X ⊃ Y) ∩ S ′.",
    "If x ̸ ∈ S ′, then x ′ ̸ ∈ X ′ ⊃ ′ Y ′, so suppose x ∈ S ′.",
    "From x ̸ ∈ X ⊃ Y, there is a z ⊑ x such that z ∈ X but z ̸ ∈ Y.Then by refinability for Y, there is a z ′ ⊑ z such that for all z ′′ ⊑ z ′, z ′′ ̸ ∈ Y.",
    "By Definition 5.52.4, since x ∈ S ′ and z ′ ⊑ x, there is a z ′′ ∈ S ′ such that z ′′ ⊑ z ′.",
    "Then by the refinability step,z ′′ ̸ ∈ Y, so z ′′ ̸ ∈ Y ′ = Y ∩ S ′, but by persistence for X, z ′′ ⊑ z ∈ X implies z ′′ ∈ X, which with z ′′ ∈ S ′ implies z ′′ ∈ X ′ = X ∩ S ′."
  ]
}